Introduction

bugAboo was a six-member South Korean girl group under A team Entertainment. They debuted on October 25, 2021, with the single album "bugAboo".

On March 7, 2019, A team Entertainment’s CEO Ryan Jhun revealed the group through an Instagram post. The same night, they performed as “ISE” or “Innocent Sexy Eyes” at the Gala Night of the 2019 Miss Malaysia pageant.

The group was expected to debut in late 2019. However, in May 2020, Ryan Jhun announced that the group’s debut was postponed from March 2020 to an unspecified date in 2021 due to the pandemic.

On December 8th, 2022, A team Entertainment announced that the members agreed to terminate their contracts, and the group was eventually disbanded.
